	     AN accident along the Table Mountain road on Saturday morning left 19 people injured after a taxi drove into a ditch. ER24 paramedics and other services arrived at 9.35am to find the taxi on the side of the road. The passengers had already climbed out of the vehicle and were walking around at the scene. Paramedics assessed the patients and found that 19 had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate, however, no serious injuries were found. Patients were treated and then taken to Northdale and Edendale hospitals. Authorities were on the scene and will be investigating further.  - Supplied. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  